Reasoning: The paper focuses on analyzing the profile metadata of Twitter users during the #LokSabhaElections2019 movement, which falls under the domain of social media analysis. The paper also investigates the spread of behavior contagion and political inclination, which can be categorized under social influence and cyber security. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques to analyze the profile changes, which can be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques to collect the profile metadata, which can be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of profile attribute change for endorsements and political movements, which can be categorized under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy).
